{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "GPT-4o's superior behavior in VideoQA (see Fig. 1 and 5), as well as the ascent of SOTA performance on benchmarks like MSVD-QA and MSRVTT-QA suggests that coarse and holistic understanding of short videos (less than 20s) are solvable by scaling up existing Video-LLMs or prompting powerful image MLLMs (like GPT-4o).",
    "Yet the understanding of fine-grained details (Xiao et al., 2021) or long-range videos (Mangalam et al., 2023; Fu et al., 2024) remains out of reach.",
    "These videos offer additional challenges that require more dedicated analysis and architecture design.",
    "One such hurdle comes from the 'needle in the haystack' problem -the search in the long video for short moments (or keyframes) that carry the correct answer.",
    "Existing benchmarks such as NExT-GQA (Xiao et al., 2024) and QAEgo4D (Datta et al., 2022) embody such challenges, yet effective techniques are lacking."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Yet the understanding of fine-grained details (Xiao et al., 2021) or long-range videos (Mangalam et al., 2023; Fu et al., 2024) remains out of reach.",
    "Existing benchmarks such as NExT-GQA (Xiao et al., 2024) and QAEgo4D (Datta et al., 2022) embody such challenges, yet effective techniques are lacking."
  ]
}